      <p>I&#039;ve worked in restaurants and what they said is true. If you employer is not following it, they are violating federal law. Wait staff can be paid a lower hourly wage as they are expected to make &#034;commission&#034; on the meal in the form of tips to make up the difference. But, at the end of the day, you have to have made federal minimum wage per hour or your employer IS required to make up that difference. And that should be based on the tips you report (which you are required to do). Not the tips you earn, bu the take home, post tipping out bartenders and busboys.</p>

