      <p>The bagel slicing thing in NY sounds ridiculous but it actually makes sense.  In NY there is no sales tax on unprepared food.  This is to help the poor buy groceries.  But there is regular sales tax on prepared foods.  So bagels at a bagel shop typically have regular sales tax, but if they sell them un-sliced, the shop can claim it is an unprepared food item and skip charging the sales tax.</p>

