      <p>We get that it is a bad system.  But, the question is if it is such a bad system why are people working in/with it?  If the credit card fees are being taken out of the tip, then the employer is screwing the workers.  Why should the customers step in to compensate for that?  Now you want people to tip on &#034;to go&#034; orders?  How about people just come by, on their way home, to give money to the waitstaff, huh?</p>
