     <div class="commentItem" id="comment-544425">
     <strong><cite class="fn">Ninety-9</cite></strong><br>

      
      <p>It can be a slap in the face, but large parties typically do take up a disproportional amount of time, on the server&#039;s part, than the same amount of people at multiple tables, especially distributing and collecting multiple payments.  Larger groups also tend to stick around longer consuming only free refills and not necessarily spending any more money.</p>
<p>If the service is bad, you talk to a manager.  Don&#039;t sweat the extra gratuity because if you really had unpleasant service, a manager will typically more than make up for it with a discount or gift card.</p>

